1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,889
We made three suggestions.

2
00:00:01,889 --> 00:00:02,769
1.

3
00:00:03,040 --> 00:00:06,369
Recognize the fact that no person is perfect.

4
00:00:06,800 --> 00:00:12,850
Some people are more nearly perfect than others, but no man is absolutely perfect.

5
00:00:13,120 --> 00:00:19,090
The most human quality about human beings is that they make mistakes, all kinds of them.

6
00:00:19,090 --> 00:00:20,290
2.

7
00:00:20,560 --> 00:00:24,769
Recognize the fact that the other fellow has a right to be different.

8
00:00:24,960 --> 00:00:27,170
Never play God about anything.

9
00:00:27,440 --> 00:00:34,129
Never dislike people because their habits are different from your own or because they prefer different clothes,

10
00:00:34,160 --> 00:00:36,930
religion, parties, or automobiles.

11
00:00:37,280 --> 00:00:43,330
You don't have to approve of what another fellow does, but you must not dislike him for doing it.

12
00:00:43,440 --> 00:00:45,249
3.

13
00:00:45,440 --> 00:00:47,410
Don't be a reformer.

14
00:00:47,600 --> 00:00:51,249
Put a little more live and let live into your philosophy.

15
00:00:51,520 --> 00:00:55,490
Most people intensely dislike being told you're wrong.

16
00:00:55,680 --> 00:01:01,090
You have a right to your own opinion, but sometimes it's better to keep it to yourself.

17
00:01:02,640 --> 00:01:06,050
Ted conscientiously applied these suggestions.

18
00:01:06,160 --> 00:01:08,690
A few months later he had a fresh outlook.

19
00:01:08,960 --> 00:01:15,490
He now accepts people for what they are, neither 100% good nor 100% bad.

20
00:01:15,920 --> 00:01:21,570
Besides, he says, the things that used to annoy the heck out of me I now find amusing.

21
00:01:21,680 --> 00:01:28,930
It finally dawned on me what a dull world this would be if people were all alike and everybody was perfect.

22
00:01:29,680 --> 00:01:32,290
Note this simple but key fact.

23
00:01:32,480 --> 00:01:36,290
No person is all good, and no person is all bad.

24
00:01:36,480 --> 00:01:39,330
The perfect person just doesn't exist.

25
00:01:39,920 --> 00:01:46,529
Now, if we let our thinking go uncontrolled, we can find much to dislike in almost anyone.

